snippet.textDisplay:
The Tesla story was a lie.
Congratulations, you bought into a story based off of something a single cop stated.
The vehicle did not have FSD and Auto-pilot could not have been enabled on the road because it didn't have road lines. On top of that, the seat belt needs to be buckled and a weight needs to be on the seat, and someone needs to tug the steering wheel every once in a while just to prevent the car from making an emergency stop and pulling over. Lastly the crash was estimated to be at 50 miles per hour and the FSD (that the car did not have installed) would only allow you to go 5mph over the speed limit.
Stop spreading fake news.
I expected more from you Anthony.
